reviews.review_text: Memories This show was my 2nd..my last show was RFK in '95..inbetween, about 75 shows..sounds great

Sweet 73 Another great example of the very jazzy groove from this peak year.  Special guests Martin Fierro and Joe Ellis (trumpet and sax respectively) really add some nice spice to the Eyes>WRS Suite at the back end of the 2d set.  The horn section really enhances the vibe and sound they were going for in that Wake of the Flood kinda way. 

A couple of things to note:  there is def. some AUD splicing in the lineage (as noted) and those SBD parts are loose at best.  It's not the high end recording that other shows from this era are.  Also, the tracking is a little quirky on Disc 3.  Let it Grow spreads out over tracks 2&3 of Disc three (the text file only notes 3 files on disc three, there are actually 4 with Sugar Mags being track 4).  Other than that, this is good stuff, the last Sing Me Back Home is also noteworth.

Recommended
Buffalo, NY  9-26-73 The missing Playing in the band can be found at www.gdlive.com in the MP-3 section.  It's worth downloading and adding to these files.

Brilliant!! Couldn't find the Playin' on the below mentioned site, but this gig is amazing. The horn section adds so, so much and it drives the band further than usual...some free jazz stuff goin' on during Eyes. Highly recommended for those into experimental jazz, free-improv stuff.
The old Aud another western NY special.  Love the HC Sunshine in the opening slot.
WRS I love some classic Weather REPORT SUITE. Its just a classic memorizing song. The harmony is just amazing its so uplifting and mellow at the same time.
